[Last week, ProMED-mail posted several Malaysian news items describing an
outbreak of flu-like illness in about 70 students in an agricultural
school, allegedly suspected to have been infected from poultry (see
20040716.1923). Avian flu was ruled out.
Reportedly, the Health Department took phlegm samples, and throat swabs,
adding that definitive tests using cultures would be completed by 23 Jul
2004 at the earliest.
No additional information regarding the said outbreak has become available
since 14 Jul 2004. The outcome of clinical and laboratory investigations,
if available, will be appreciated. - Mod.AS].
